SENATE RESOLUTION NO. 206
BY SENATOR MIZELL
COMMENDATIONS. Commends Courtney McCool Griffeth upon being inducted into the
2026 class of the USA Gymnastics Hall of Fame.
1 A RESOLUTION
2 To commend Courtney McCool Griffeth, Olympian, NCAA champion, and coach, upon
3 being inducted into the 2026 class of the USA Gymnastics Hall of Fame.
4 WHEREAS, Courtney McCool Griffeth, Olympian, collegiate gymnast, and coach,
5 will be honored, recognized, and inducted as a member of the 2026 class of the USA
6 Gymnastics Hall of Fame on Saturday, August 8, 2026, in conjunction with the 2026 Xfinity
7 U.S. Gymnastics Championships and National Congress and Trade Show in Phoenix,
8 Arizona; and
9 WHEREAS, a 2004 Olympian and NCAA champion and coach, Courtney McCool
10 Griffeth, is being celebrated for her contributions to women's artistic gymnastics, which
11 includes a decorated career as an elite and collegiate athlete; and
12 WHEREAS, following a strong performance at the U.S. Olympic Trials, Courtney
13 earned a coveted spot on Team USA to compete in the 2004 Olympics in Athens, Greece,
14 earning a silver medal in the team competition; and
15 WHEREAS, leading up to the Olympic games, Courtney earned high marks at the
16 2003 Pan American Games in Santo Domingo, Dominican Republic, contributing to the
17 team's gold medal and placing second in the vault, and at the 2004 U.S. National
18 Championships, she claimed a silver medal on floor and earned a bronze medal on beam;
